Answer any questions

His Majesty’s Treasury (HMT) is led by the Chancellor of the Exchequer [5iC]: dz?.
as well as their deputy (the Exchequer Secretary [6iC]).
Its purpose is managing UK finances and paid perks, as well as regulating the VIP badge.

The Ministry of Justice’s job is to schedule and keep record of all hearings within the UK,
as well as keeping an up to date archive of all disciplinary actions.
Hearings may be held for breach of law,
or to interpret a piece of legislation where definitions are muddy or unclear.
It is led by the Justice Secretary [5iC]: dreckly,
as well as their deputy, the Attorney General [6iC].

The rest of the departments are led by a Secretary of State [5iC], whose deputy is a 6iC Minister.

The Foreign, Commonwealth and Development Office (Foreign Office/FCDO) is responsible for:
creating and keeping good relations with other agencies, as well as forming alliances.
The Foreign Office also oversees the MI6 division of the MI branch,
and manages the Foreign Service Officer (FSO) team.
FSOs are volunteers who visit other agencies and report back to the Foreign Office.
8iC+ MI6 agents are de facto Foreign Security Agents (FSAs); their role is similar to that of FSO.
The current Foreign Sec. is: EpicMorilecrime; the Foreign Minister is playergurl.
